# Conventional Commits

When generating git commit messages for this workspace, always follow the Conventional Commits specification.

## Required format

- Use: `<type>(<optional-scope>): <subject>`
- Keep the subject concise and imperative (e.g. "add pricing badge", "fix auth redirect loop")
- Do not end the subject with a period
- Use lowercase types

## Allowed types

- `feat` for new features
- `fix` for bug fixes
- `revert` for reverting a previous commit
- `chore` for maintenance tasks not affecting product behavior
- `docs` for documentation-only changes
- `refactor` for code changes that do not change behavior
- `test` for adding or updating tests
- `perf` for performance improvements
- `build` for build system or dependency changes
- `ci` for CI/CD configuration changes
- `style` for formatting-only changes (no logic changes)

## Selection guidance

- Prefer `feat` when user-facing behavior is added
- Prefer `fix` when behavior is corrected
- Prefer `chore` for tooling/config/cleanup work
- Prefer `revert` when the change explicitly undoes an earlier commit

## Examples

- `feat(home): add recipe cards preview section`
- `fix(theme): resolve dark mode toggle hydration mismatch`
- `chore(config): align workspace lint settings`
- `revert: revert "feat(auth): add social login buttons"`
